2
00:00:54,187 --> 00:00:57,187
多谢你能来见我 芬顿先生
Thank you for agreeing to meet with me, Mr Fenton.

3
00:00:59,187 --> 00:01:01,255
莫里知道你来这么? 
Does Moray know you're here?

4
00:01:01,256 --> 00:01:03,186
不知道 先生 按之前的约定
No, sir. As we agreed,

5
00:01:03,187 --> 00:01:07,187
这场会面只有你知我知
this meeting is between you and I.

6
00:01:37,913 --> 00:01:38,913
我好像还不能走
I can't seem to leave.

7
00:01:39,262 --> 00:01:42,261
总有做不完的事
There's always something else to do.

8
00:01:42,262 --> 00:01:44,261
我只是想为上任的第一天做好准备
I just want to be prepared for my first day.

9
00:01:44,262 --> 00:01:46,262
噢 你行的
Oh, I don't doubt you will be.

10
00:01:49,262 --> 00:01:52,119
你是来祝我好运的? 
Have you come to wish me luck?

11
00:01:52,120 --> 00:01:54,262
你要是需要的话
 I would, if I thought you needed it.

12
00:02:03,262 --> 00:02:08,262
- 我们如愿以偿了 - 是的 差不多
- We have everything we wished for. - Yes. Almost.

13
00:02:23,262 --> 00:02:25,261
抱歉 艾德蒙 我能帮什么忙?
I'm sorry, Edmund. What could I do?!

14
00:02:25,262 --> 00:02:28,261
我看见门被砸碎了 来里头看看
I saw the door was smashed, had a look inside

15
00:02:28,262 --> 00:02:33,262
却没有人 就只好叫你来了
but I couldn't see anyone. So all I could think of was send for you.

16
00:02:37,262 --> 00:02:39,261
你觉得是谁干的?
Who do you think it was?

17
00:02:39,262 --> 00:02:41,261
窃贼? 不像是偷了很多东西的模样 是吧?
Robbers? Doesn't look like they've taken much, does it?

18
00:02:41,262 --> 00:02:43,356
我经营这家店多少年了 
How many years have I taken care of this shop,

19
00:02:43,357 --> 00:02:45,261
从无到有一点点地积累
 built it up from nothing?

20
00:02:45,262 --> 00:02:48,621
我的小店 洛维特的帷帐 
My shop. Lovett's Drapery.

21
00:02:48,622 --> 00:02:52,261
看这一团糟! 谁会做这事?
 Look at this! Who would do this?

22
00:02:52,262 --> 00:02:52,976
是谁闯进来
Who would come in here 

23
00:02:52,977 --> 00:02:55,261
这么肆意践踏一个男人的心头肉?!
and not give a care for a man's life?!

24
00:02:55,262 --> 00:02:57,261
我们会整理好的 然后修好门!
We'll tidy it up, get the glass fixed!

25
00:02:57,262 --> 00:02:59,261
再然后我就满心担忧地回到我的小屋去
But then I go back to my cottage with a head full of worries.

26
00:02:59,262 --> 00:03:01,261
那干脆卖了它不就好啦 是不是?
You'll just have to sell it then, won't ya?

27
00:03:01,262 --> 00:03:04,262
是不是林子大了什么鸟都有 山姆?
What kind of people live in this world now, Sam?

28
00:03:13,262 --> 00:03:14,261
德妮丝!
Denise!

29
00:03:14,262 --> 00:03:18,261
我... 我可不会假装这是我人生中
I'm... Look, I'm not going to pretend that this is the happiest

30
00:03:18,262 --> 00:03:19,261
最快乐的一天
day of me life.

31
00:03:19,262 --> 00:03:21,261
我也不会说我觉得这很公平
I'm not going to stand here and say I think it's fair,

32
00:03:21,262 --> 00:03:23,261
因为老实说...
because honestly...

33
00:03:23,262 --> 00:03:26,261
哎呦喂 注意喽 德妮丝 梅尔托在找你呢
Oh, you'd better watch out, Denise. Myrtle's looking for you.

34
00:03:26,262 --> 00:03:30,261
我想她一定给你特制了一份腌鱼
I do believe that she got hold of a kipper especially for you.

35
00:03:30,262 --> 00:03:32,261
我只想告诉你...
Look, I just want you to know that...

36
00:03:32,262 --> 00:03:33,896
噢! 差点忘了 你叔叔回来了
Oh! Nearly forgot. Your uncle's back. 

37
00:03:33,897 --> 00:03:36,261
但小店出了点问题
Problem at the shop.

38
00:03:36,262 --> 00:03:39,461
瞧 一直以来我都知道我没希望 就像...
Look, I knew all along I didn't stand a chance, like, so...

39
00:03:39,462 --> 00:03:42,261
早 我都搞不清自己是饿还是不饿了
Morning. I don't know whether I'm hungry or not hungry.

40
00:03:42,262 --> 00:03:46,262
我太激动了 可否亲吻一下女装部主管呢?
I'm so excited. Am I allowed to kiss the Head of Ladieswear?

41
00:03:47,262 --> 00:03:50,261
我永远也不会像你俩那么出色 但是我可以说
I'll never be as fine as you two, but I can say now,

42
00:03:50,262 --> 00:03:52,261
苏西・贝尔 来自女装部
Susy Bell - Ladieswear.

43
00:03:52,262 --> 00:03:56,261
- 那对我来说就够威风了 - 你在这儿!
- Well, that's fine enough for me. - There you are!

44
00:03:56,262 --> 00:03:57,826
我给你煮了一份腌鱼 真他娘的好吃  
I have cooked a bloody lovely kipper for you 

45
00:03:57,827 --> 00:03:59,261
但要变得真他娘的冷了
and it's going bloody cold.

46
00:03:59,262 --> 00:04:01,261
我马上就去 梅尔托
I'll be along in a minute, Myrtle.

47
00:04:01,262 --> 00:04:04,261
不是因为你有权把我调去店里而奉承你的
I'm not doing this because you're in a position to put me front of house.

48
00:04:04,262 --> 00:04:05,430
我永远不会干这种事
I would never do such a thing.

49
00:04:05,431 --> 00:04:07,261
早 梅尔托! 我也在呢!
Morning, Myrtle! I'm here too!

50
00:04:07,262 --> 00:04:11,261
碰巧手边有腌鱼就做了 就这样而已
Just happened to get me hands on a kipper, that's all.

51
00:04:11,262 --> 00:04:12,261
好吧 在亚瑟向你脱帽致意之前
Well, I'd better say it quick,

52
00:04:12,262 --> 00:04:15,261
我得速战速决
before Arthur comes doffing his cap at you.

53
00:04:15,262 --> 00:04:19,262
我不会为难你 只是 尽量...
Look, I won't make it difficult for you. Just, try and...

54
00:04:20,262 --> 00:04:23,261
我发现真的挺难接受 如果你对我说...
I'd find it really hard if you spoke to me...

55
00:04:23,262 --> 00:04:26,565
克莱拉 我不会一夜之间就变成奥德丽女士
Clara, I'm not going to turn into Miss Audrey overnight.

56
00:04:26,566 --> 00:04:27,261
我保证
 I promise.

57
00:04:27,262 --> 00:04:28,261
以后还需要请你多多关照
I'm going to need your help.

58
00:04:28,262 --> 00:04:32,261
可最重要的是 我从来都不想失去你
But most of all, I never want to lose your friendship.

59
00:04:32,262 --> 00:04:35,261
德妮丝! 你的腌鱼!
Denise! Kippers!

60
00:04:35,262 --> 00:04:37,443
我压根就不喜欢腌鱼 
I don't even LIKE kippers.

61
00:04:37,444 --> 00:04:39,262
苏西肯定能帮上忙
 - I'm sure Susy'll help you out.

62
00:04:51,262 --> 00:04:53,261
你在我店里干什么?
What are you doing in my shop?

63
00:04:53,262 --> 00:04:55,386
听见没? 你在我商店干什么?!
Did you hear me? What are you doing in my shop?!

64
00:04:55,387 --> 00:04:56,261
当时又没人
It was empty.

65
00:04:56,262 --> 00:04:58,261
你打破了门! 看看你做的好事!
You broke the door! Look at the mess you've made!

66
00:04:58,262 --> 00:05:01,262
哪条沟里来的滚回哪去! 你听见没?!
Get back to the gutter you came from! Do you hear me?!

67
00:05:05,262 --> 00:05:07,262
- 上帝保佑你 - 滚蛋!
- God bless you. - Get out!

68
00:05:12,262 --> 00:05:15,261
真是难以置信地乏味 他们谈论的尽是
It's tedious beyond belief. All they talk of is

69
00:05:15,262 --> 00:05:18,261
会热卖的是印花还是条纹
whether prints or stripes will sell,

70
00:05:18,262 --> 00:05:21,761
这个秋天哪种丝绸会热销
what kind of silk might sell this autumn.

71
00:05:21,762 --> 00:05:23,160
爸爸 凯瑟琳跟我说 
Papa, Katherine told me how, when she was a girl, 

72
00:05:23,171 --> 00:05:24,261
她小时候常常
she used to

73
00:05:24,262 --> 00:05:28,261
跑到森林里去找神秘人
run off into the woods here searching for The Secret People.

74
00:05:28,262 --> 00:05:31,261
神秘人是我想象出来的朋友
The Secret People were my imaginary friends.

75
00:05:31,262 --> 00:05:33,948
对独生子女的孤独的一种慰藉 
An only child's compensations for her loneliness. 

76
00:05:33,959 --> 00:05:36,261
- 爸爸 我们能... - 沿街扩建店面
- Papa, could we...? - It was Moray's intention

77
00:05:36,262 --> 00:05:38,262
是莫里的主意 没错吧?
to expand along the whole street, wasn't it?

78
00:05:40,262 --> 00:05:45,262
汤姆 亲爱的 芙罗拉在问你问题
Tom, my darling, Flora was asking you a question.

79
00:05:47,262 --> 00:05:50,261
你的问题是什么 芙罗拉?
What is your question, Flora?

80
00:05:50,262 --> 00:05:53,308
我喜欢听凯瑟琳讲她少女时期的故事
I loved hearing about when Katherine was a girl.

81
00:05:53,309 --> 00:05:56,262
你能不能也给我讲讲你年轻的时候
 Would you tell me about when you were a boy?

82
00:05:58,262 --> 00:05:59,262
大概可以
Possibly.

83
00:06:02,262 --> 00:06:07,261
我认为我们应该在莫里没做到的点上找突破口
I think we should do what Moray so patently failed to achieve.

84
00:06:08,262 --> 00:06:11,261
我有三个目标 第一个是找机会重返天堂百货
I have three objectives - to find a way back into the store.

85
00:06:11,262 --> 00:06:13,261
- 你做到了 - 是"我们"做到的
- You've done that. - WE'VE done that.

86
00:06:13,262 --> 00:06:15,261
没你里应外合 什么事都完不成
Nothing would be possible without you keeping it together here.

87
00:06:15,262 --> 00:06:18,261
另外两个是 筹集资金 然后劝服
And the other two are, to find the funds, and persuade

88
00:06:18,262 --> 00:06:21,261
- 威斯顿夫妇卖了商店 - 卖给我
- Mr and Mrs Weston to sell. - To sell to me.

89
00:06:21,262 --> 00:06:23,261
莫里先生 达德利先生
Mr Moray. Mr Dudley.

90
00:06:23,262 --> 00:06:25,261
我有个关于女装部促销的建议
I have a proposal for a promotion in Ladieswear.

91
00:06:25,262 --> 00:06:28,261
点子来得挺快啊
You didn't waste much time.

92
00:06:28,262 --> 00:06:33,030
下午茶 实际上 是办个茶宴 
Afternoon tea. Indeed, a tea party. 

93
00:06:33,131 --> 00:06:35,261
放些桌子 铺上洁白的桌布
Tables. With white tablecloths.

94
00:06:35,262 --> 00:06:37,261
加上茗茶 蛋糕和烤饼
Fine teas. Cakes and scones.

95
00:06:37,262 --> 00:06:40,261
女士们会被吸引进来 然后坐下闲聊...
The ladies would come in, to sit and gossip...

96
00:06:40,262 --> 00:06:42,261
那由谁来上蛋糕和茗茶?
And who would serve the cakes and fine teas?

97
00:06:42,262 --> 00:06:44,262
梅尔托可以
I thought Myrtle.

98
00:06:45,262 --> 00:06:48,261
不错! 你心肠真好 德妮丝
Right! Oh, it is good-hearted of you, Denise.

99
00:06:48,262 --> 00:06:51,261
我们都知道梅尔托唠叨着调到店里来的事
We all know that Myrtle nags away to come front of house.

100
00:06:51,262 --> 00:06:54,261
但是好心肠可不是运作一个部门最需要的品质
But good-heartedness is not the best quality for running a department.

101
00:06:54,262 --> 00:06:57,594
梅尔托绝不能派去服务我们的客户 
Myrtle must never be let loose on our customers.

102
00:06:57,595 --> 00:06:59,261
女装部上蛋糕?!
 Cakes in Ladieswear?!

103
00:06:59,262 --> 00:07:03,779
你真以为那是我们苦心要塑造的形象吗?
Do you honestly suppose - that is the impression we are trying to make?

104
00:07:03,790 --> 00:07:05,261
不是 先生
No, sir.

105
00:07:05,265 --> 00:07:08,261
就这样吧
No. Right.

106
00:07:08,262 --> 00:07:09,928
事实就这样 德妮丝 
It's true, Denise, what he says.

107
00:07:09,929 --> 00:07:12,261
他没说错 你需要立刻进入角色
 You need to step into the role now.

108
00:07:12,262 --> 00:07:14,261
那意味着你做的决定可能不招人喜爱
That means making decisions that others won't like.

109
00:07:14,262 --> 00:07:16,261
你必须自信坚定
You have to be strong.

110
00:07:16,264 --> 00:07:17,179
最终 他们一定会尊重你
In the end, they will respect you, 

111
00:07:17,180 --> 00:07:18,200
但是一开始
but to begin with,

112
00:07:18,201 --> 00:07:21,262
你不能总担心他们是否喜欢你
 you can't let yourself worry whether they'll like you or not.

113
00:07:47,262 --> 00:07:50,261
德妮丝小姐 这些帽子是要展览的吗?
Miss Denise, are these hats to go on display?

114
00:07:50,262 --> 00:07:52,261
是的 苏西 放在窗户旁边
Yes, Susy. Put them by the window.

115
00:07:52,262 --> 00:07:55,261
德妮丝小姐 我该把它们都取出来吗 女士?
Miss Denise, shall I put all of them out, ma'am?

116
00:07:55,262 --> 00:07:56,261
对了! 德妮丝小姐
Oh! Miss Denise,

117
00:07:56,262 --> 00:07:59,261
我是否需要给试衣间添些鲜花?
shall I fetch some fresh flowers for the changing closet?

118
00:07:59,262 --> 00:08:02,261
摆弄鲜花一向是克莱拉喜爱的活
Clara usually likes to do the flowers.

119
00:08:02,262 --> 00:08:04,262
来吧 我们一起去取花
Come on, we'll fetch them together.

120
00:08:08,262 --> 00:08:11,262
德妮丝小姐 梅尔托在找你
Miss Denise, Myrtle's asking for you.

121
00:08:14,262 --> 00:08:15,566
但是你答应了的 
But you promised.

122
00:08:15,567 --> 00:08:17,262
我说了我试过了 梅尔托
 I said I'd try, Myrtle.

123
00:08:18,262 --> 00:08:20,625
好吧 你没有尽力 对吧? 
Well, you didn't try hard enough, did you?

124
00:08:20,626 --> 00:08:22,261
苏西都有了个职位
 Susy has a position.

125
00:08:22,262 --> 00:08:24,261
怎么苏西有的我就没有?
What's Susy got that I haven't?

126
00:08:24,263 --> 00:08:25,261
就因为她是你室友 对吗?
She shared a room with you, is that it?

127
00:08:25,262 --> 00:08:27,326
我真的很希望我们依然是朋友
I so want us to remain friends.

128
00:08:27,327 --> 00:08:29,261
朋友? 朋友是这么当的?
Friends? Is that what you call it?

129
00:08:29,262 --> 00:08:31,261
你对我来说是朋友
I know I'm a friend to you.

130
00:08:31,262 --> 00:08:33,261
我就不确定你是否当我是朋友了 因为
I'm not so sure you're a friend to me, now that

131
00:08:33,262 --> 00:08:36,261
你名字后还有个"小姐"尊称呢
you have a Miss before your name.

132
00:08:36,262 --> 00:08:39,261
好了 我还有活要干 德妮丝"小姐"
Well, I have work to do, MISS Denise.

133
00:08:39,262 --> 00:08:41,262
炉子得擦干净
There's stoves to be scrubbed.

134
00:08:55,262 --> 00:08:58,261
这个旧理发店收购了有一年多了是吗?
This old barber's shop was purchased over a year ago, I understand?

135
00:08:58,262 --> 00:09:01,261
是的先生 本是计划着扩展店面用
Yes, sir. I believe the plan was to expand.

136
00:09:01,262 --> 00:09:03,261
那怎么现在是这个样子?
Then why does it stand like this?

137
00:09:03,262 --> 00:09:06,261
莫里先生重新考虑了 先生
Mr Moray reconsidered it, sir.

138
00:09:06,262 --> 00:09:07,690
叫他到这来见我 
Ask him to come out here to join me. 

139
00:09:07,691 --> 00:09:09,261
恐怕莫里先生这会儿
I'm afraid Mr Moray's

140
00:09:09,262 --> 00:09:12,261
去见我们的供应商了 先生
gone out to meet with one of our suppliers, sir.

141
00:09:12,262 --> 00:09:15,261
- 要多久? - 我不知道
- How long will he be? - I don't know.

142
00:09:15,262 --> 00:09:18,261
也许他约见的不止一个
I think perhaps he is visiting more than one merchant.

143
00:09:18,262 --> 00:09:20,262
那我就等着
Then I will wait.

144
00:09:26,262 --> 00:09:28,661
嘿 看这个老巫婆 
Hey, look at this old witch.

145
00:09:28,662 --> 00:09:30,261
从这都能闻到她的味道
Ugh, smell her from here.

146
00:09:30,262 --> 00:09:32,261
你觉得她是要进去买件皮草吗?
Do you think she's coming in to buy a fur?

147
00:09:32,262 --> 00:09:34,262
我们该问问她 给她量量尺寸
We should ask her. Measure her up.

148
00:10:09,262 --> 00:10:12,262
很抱歉当时对你那种态度 我做得太过了
I'm sorry I spoke to you that way. There was no call for that.

149
00:10:13,262 --> 00:10:16,262
你饿吗?
Are you hungry?

150
00:10:32,430 --> 00:10:35,261
你想要的很明显 莫里
It's clear what you want, Moray.

151
00:10:35,262 --> 00:10:37,261
你和我都渴...渴望同样的事
You c-crave the same thing as I do.

152
00:10:37,262 --> 00:10:42,261
威斯顿夫妇挡着咱...咱们的路了
Mr and Mrs Weston stand in the way of b-both of us, do they not?

153
00:10:42,262 --> 00:10:46,261
也许在这件事上我们有着相同的利益
Perhaps you and I may be of benefit to one another in this matter.

154
00:10:46,262 --> 00:10:49,261
这件事怎么行得通 芬顿先生?
How might that be possible, Mr Fenton?

