Perhaps that tunic has memories for him.

319
00:20:24,262 --> 00:20:25,262
战争的记忆
Memories of the war.

320
00:20:27,262 --> 00:20:30,261
这是我的错 让我来弥补吧
I made a mistake. Let me make it up to you.

321
00:20:30,262 --> 00:20:32,261
我们来弥补下 你和我 就在早上
We'll have a treat. You and I. In the morning.

322
00:20:32,262 --> 00:20:35,261
我们做些什么 去骑马吗
What shall we do? Shall we go riding?

323
00:20:35,262 --> 00:20:38,262
- 或者去野餐 - 去天堂百货
- Perhaps a picnic? - The... The Paradise.

324
00:20:39,262 --> 00:20:42,261
没错 我们去天堂百货
Yes. We'll go to The Paradise

325
00:20:42,262 --> 00:20:44,262
去好好放纵一下
and we will indulge ourselves.

326
00:20:52,262 --> 00:20:53,262
晚安 苏西
Good night, Susy.

327
00:21:21,262 --> 00:21:23,262
你在这儿干什么
WHAT are you doing here?

328
00:21:26,262 --> 00:21:29,261
- 我来看你 孩子 - 我不希望你在这儿
- I've come to see you, child. - I don't want you here.

329
00:21:29,262 --> 00:21:32,261
你不能给你妈一个道歉的机会吗?
Can you not give your ma a chance to say that she's sorry?

330
00:21:32,262 --> 00:21:35,261
道歉 我应该相信吗?
"Sorry"? Am I supposed to believe that?

331
00:21:35,262 --> 00:21:38,261
这么多年 你就想说句对不起吗?
All these years and that's all you want "sorry"?

332
00:21:38,262 --> 00:21:39,261
我一直在找你
I've been looking for you.

333
00:21:39,262 --> 00:21:41,261
我没那么难找 贝拉姑姑知道我在哪儿
I'm not so hard to find. Aunt Bella knows where I am.

334
00:21:41,262 --> 00:21:44,261
我没有一天不在想我的女儿
There's not a day goes by where I don't think about my girl!

335
00:21:44,262 --> 00:21:46,261
要我告诉你我怎么想的吗?
Shall I tell you what I think of?

336
00:21:46,262 --> 00:21:51,261
我自己的声音祈求你不要离开我 不要让我走
My own voice pleading with you not to leave me, not to let me go.

337
00:21:51,262 --> 00:21:55,261
我亲妈却喝得太醉听不到
And my own mother too drunk to hear me.

338
00:21:55,262 --> 00:21:57,261
甚至不会亲我
Too drunk to even KISS me.

339
00:21:57,262 --> 00:22:00,262
我现在有了自己的生活 而你不在其中
I have a life now, and you are no part of it!

340
00:22:02,262 --> 00:22:07,261
跟我进去 来吧 跟我进去坐坐
Come inside with me. Come on. Come and sit with me.

341
00:22:07,262 --> 00:22:11,261
让你妈妈好好看看你 就一晚
Let your ma feast her eyes on her beautiful girl just for one night.

342
00:22:11,262 --> 00:22:14,261
坐在一起看你喝酒
Sit with you while you drink,

343
00:22:14,262 --> 00:22:17,262
听你讲故事骗我让我相信你不算坏吗
tell me some story that will trick me into believing you're not so bad?

344
00:22:19,262 --> 00:22:24,261
我妈妈对我撒谎 一向如此 她满嘴谎话
My mother lied to me. That's what she does, she lies.

345
00:22:24,262 --> 00:22:26,261
你去喝吧 妈
You go and drink, Ma.

346
00:22:26,262 --> 00:22:29,261
喝了多少瓶才会忘了自己曾有个女儿?!
How many glasses till you forget you even HAVE a daughter?!

347
00:22:29,262 --> 00:22:32,261
你去喝个够吧
You... you go and drink your fill.

348
00:22:32,262 --> 00:22:33,690
如果你还有慈悲之心 
If you have any mercy,

349
00:22:33,691 --> 00:22:35,261
今晚就沿着这条街一直走
 you will walk down that street tonight

350
00:22:35,262 --> 00:22:36,262
永远不要回来
and NEVER come back!

351
00:23:32,262 --> 00:23:35,262
有些事情我们自认为无法承受
There are things we believe we cannot bear.

352
00:23:36,262 --> 00:23:38,262
但其实我们可以
But we can bear them.

353
00:23:39,262 --> 00:23:41,262
我们可以承受
We do bear them.

354
00:24:03,262 --> 00:24:04,261
早上好
Morning.

355
00:24:04,262 --> 00:24:07,261
我们得让你女儿看到最好的你
We need your daughter to see you looking at your best,

356
00:24:07,262 --> 00:24:10,261
让她知道你病好了 恢复了
if she's to know you're back on your feet and well again.

357
00:24:10,262 --> 00:24:12,261
你人真好
That is kind of ya.

358
00:24:12,262 --> 00:24:14,261
你可以去后面洗漱一下
You can wash and clean up in the back.

359
00:24:14,262 --> 00:24:16,261
这是我最爱的颜色
It's me favourite colour.

360
00:24:16,262 --> 00:24:19,262
我已经很多年没穿过新的漂亮的衣服了
It's many years since I wore a dress new and pretty.

361
00:24:21,262 --> 00:24:26,261
拉比 我得回到我妻子身边了
Ruby, I need to be getting back to my wife.

362
00:24:26,262 --> 00:24:29,261
我们刚结婚 在海边有一间小屋
I'm newly married. We have a cottage by the sea.

363
00:24:29,262 --> 00:24:33,261
我不能呆在这儿了 所以我怎么安排你好呢?
I can't stay here. So what are we to do with you?

364
00:24:33,262 --> 00:24:35,261
我没地方去
I've nowhere to go.

365
00:24:35,262 --> 00:24:37,262
你女儿呢 跟她谈过了吗?
What about your daughter? If you talk to her?

366
00:24:42,262 --> 00:24:45,261
我会穿上这衣服 让我看起来精神点
I'll put the dress on and I'll smart meself up.

367
00:24:45,262 --> 00:24:48,262
她会看到我不再那么体弱多病了
And she will see that I'm not sickly no more.

368
00:24:50,262 --> 00:24:53,262
你确定你没事吗?
Are you sure you're well enough?

369
00:24:55,262 --> 00:25:00,261
如果我能留下 直到和她说话
If I could stay until such time as I speak with her.

370
00:25:00,262 --> 00:25:02,261
我想保持最好的状态
I would like to be at my best.

371
00:25:02,262 --> 00:25:05,262
当然 你当然可以
Course. Course you can.

372
00:25:10,262 --> 00:25:12,261
乔纳斯
Jonas!

373
00:25:12,262 --> 00:25:13,262
我想和你谈谈
I want to talk with you.

374
00:25:17,262 --> 00:25:18,636
汤姆・威斯顿在考虑...
Tom Weston is considering...

375
00:25:18,637 --> 00:25:20,261
他打算扩张商店 先生
 He intends to develop the store, sir.

376
00:25:23,262 --> 00:25:26,261
如果我要求进一步与芬顿先生谈谈
If I were to request further discussions with Mr Fenton...

377
00:25:26,262 --> 00:25:28,261
如果您愿意的话 我可以今天为你安排 先生
I could arrange that for you today, if you wish, sir.

378
00:25:28,262 --> 00:25:30,261
或只是给他带个信
Or I could simply convey a message to him

379
00:25:30,262 --> 00:25:33,261
说您愿意重新考虑他的要求
saying you're willing to reconsider his offer.

380
00:25:33,262 --> 00:25:36,262
如果您真的愿意重新考虑
If you are indeed willing to reconsider his proposition?

381
00:25:37,262 --> 00:25:39,261
我们如何
How would we, er...?

382
00:25:39,262 --> 00:25:41,737
威斯顿先生是个反复无常的人
Mr Weston is a volatile man, sir.

383
00:25:41,738 --> 00:25:43,261
他做事比较轻率
 He is capable of behaving rashly.

384
00:25:43,262 --> 00:25:45,261
甚至粗暴
Wildly, even.

385
00:25:45,262 --> 00:25:49,261
那你猜他会轻率地解雇我还是粗暴地摆脱我?
Suppose he rashly dismisses me, or wildly decides to get rid of me?

386
00:25:49,262 --> 00:25:50,716
让我说的话 先生
If I may, sir, 

387
00:25:50,719 --> 00:25:52,262
他的妻子不会让这一切发生的
his wife would not permit that to happen.

388
00:25:54,262 --> 00:25:57,261
是 是 我明白
Yes. Yes, I understand.

389
00:25:57,262 --> 00:26:01,262
您需要我去联系芬顿先生吗
Do you wish me to contact Mr Fenton, sir?

390
00:26:03,262 --> 00:26:04,262
是的
I do.

391
00:26:10,262 --> 00:26:11,261
我要让大家看看...
I will show 'em all...

392
00:26:11,262 --> 00:26:15,261
我要让莫里先生知道他错了 让达德利先生
I'll show Mr Moray he was wrong. I'll show Mr Dudley

393
00:26:15,262 --> 00:26:18,261
知道我真正的模样
what I am truly made of.

394
00:26:18,262 --> 00:26:21,261
我看起来美吧 本就这样
Well, don't I look pretty? Made for it.

395
00:26:21,262 --> 00:26:24,262
管好你的嘴 不然大家都跟你一起丢人
Well, just watch your mouth or you'll put us all to shame.

396
00:26:28,262 --> 00:26:31,261
德妮丝 随她去吧
Denise! Erm, leave her be.

397
00:26:31,262 --> 00:26:34,262
她准备好了会来找你的
She'll come to you when she's ready to.

398
00:26:36,262 --> 00:26:37,897
威斯顿夫人 芙罗拉小姐 
Mrs Weston! Miss Flora.

399
00:26:37,898 --> 00:26:39,261
什么风把您二位吹来了
 What brings you to see us today?

400
00:26:39,262 --> 00:26:41,261
我打算让芙罗拉今早好好玩玩
I am intent on spoiling Flora this morning.

401
00:26:41,262 --> 00:26:43,261
那您来对地方了 夫人
Then you have come to the right place, ma'am.

402
00:26:43,262 --> 00:26:45,261
你将享受我们最棒的服务
You shall receive only the finest service from our ladies,

403
00:26:45,262 --> 00:26:47,261
我向您保证
I can assure you.

404
00:26:47,262 --> 00:26:48,976
威斯顿夫人 
Mrs Weston.

405
00:26:48,977 --> 00:26:53,261
呃 凯瑟琳 抱歉 我忘乎所以了
 Er, Katherine. Forgive me, I forgot myself.

406
00:26:53,262 --> 00:26:55,262
您今天非常美丽动人
May I say how lovely you look today?

407
00:26:57,262 --> 00:27:00,261
我的意思是 商店的大门永远向你敞开
What I mean is, it's always a delight to see you in the store.

408
00:27:00,262 --> 00:27:01,261
还有你 芙罗拉小姐
And you, Miss Flora.

409
00:27:02,262 --> 00:27:03,690
凯瑟琳 既然你来了 
Since you're here, Katherine,

410
00:27:03,695 --> 00:27:05,261
可以和我一起喝杯咖啡吗?
perhaps you'll join me

411
00:27:05,263 --> 00:27:08,261
还有你的丈夫 如果他也来了的话
for coffee. And your husband, if he is to visit us today?

412
00:27:08,262 --> 00:27:12,261
你今天心情很好啊 莫里
You're in fine spirits today, Moray.

413
00:27:12,262 --> 00:27:14,261
我承蒙你的关照
I owe you the courtesy of kindness.

414
00:27:14,262 --> 00:27:16,261
虽然你没有必要非得答应
You do not owe me any such consideration,

415
00:27:16,262 --> 00:27:19,262
但如果有这机会我会很感激
but I'd be grateful for the chance to earn your forbearance.

416
00:27:24,262 --> 00:27:27,261
我很高兴和你一起喝咖啡
I'd be delighted to join you for coffee.

417
00:27:27,262 --> 00:27:28,261
芙罗拉!
Flora!

418
00:27:28,262 --> 00:27:30,262
加了肉桂的咖啡
Coffee. With cinnamon.

419
00:27:45,262 --> 00:27:48,261
威斯顿夫人 女士 芙罗拉小姐
Mrs Weston. Ma'am. Miss Flora.

420
00:27:48,262 --> 00:27:51,261
我希望你今天尽管宠着芙罗拉 德妮丝
I want you to utterly spoil Flora today, Denise.

421
00:27:51,262 --> 00:27:53,341
她想要什么就给她什么 
Anything she wants, she can have.

422
00:27:53,342 --> 00:27:55,261
这是我们的荣幸 夫人
It would be our pleasure, ma'am.

423
00:27:55,262 --> 00:27:57,262
苏西 请招待这位年轻的女士
Susy, please attend to the young lady.

424
00:28:00,262 --> 00:28:03,262
我和莫里喝咖啡的这段时间 她就交给你了
I will leave it with you while I have a coffee with Moray.

425
00:28:09,262 --> 00:28:12,261
我想要一件这种有羽毛的衣服
I want one of these dresses with the feathers.

426
00:28:12,262 --> 00:28:15,261
恐怕这些礼服是给大人穿的 小孩不能穿
I'm afraid these gowns are for adults, not children.

427
00:28:15,262 --> 00:28:17,261
但我想要
But I want one.

428
00:28:17,262 --> 00:28:19,732
让我给你看一些
Let me show you some of the things

429
00:28:19,733 --> 00:28:23,261
更适合小女孩的东西
 we have that might be more suitable for a girl.

430
00:28:23,262 --> 00:28:27,455
我设想了一下把扩展区建成珠宝部的事
I had myself thought of making the extension a jewellery department.

431
00:28:27,457 --> 00:28:30,229
我想象客人们在街道上走时
I imagined that as customers approached along the street

432
00:28:30,230 --> 00:28:32,261
他们最先看到的
the first thing they would see

433
00:28:32,262 --> 00:28:36,261
是充满了贵气和色彩的橱窗
would be windows bursting with colours and extravagance.

434
00:28:36,262 --> 00:28:39,261
但光是储存展品的费用就超出了我的预算
But the cost of stocking the display alone was beyond me.

435
00:28:39,262 --> 00:28:43,261
不过 现在情况不同了
However, things are different now.

436
00:28:43,262 --> 00:28:45,211
咖啡还可以吗 凯瑟琳?
How's your coffee, Katherine?

437
00:28:45,219 --> 00:28:48,261
不错 很美味
It's fine. It's delicious.

438
00:28:48,262 --> 00:28:51,261
我第一次发现肉桂咖啡是在 呃  
I first discovered cinnamon coffee whilst in, erm,

439
00:28:51,262 --> 00:28:54,261
印度 对吧 凯瑟琳?
was it India, Katherine?

440
00:28:54,262 --> 00:28:56,261
- 不 不 我想是摩洛哥 - 是在锡兰
- No, no, no, I think it was Morocco. - It was Ceylon.

441
00:28:56,262 --> 00:29:00,261
对 对 我费尽口舌才说服凯瑟琳尝尝
Yes, yes! I had the devil to convince Katherine to try it,

442
00:29:00,262 --> 00:29:02,262
但她喝过一次之后 就再也喝不够了 
but once she did, she could never have enough.

443
00:29:05,262 --> 00:29:08,262
你喝咖啡的时候还会放肉桂吗? 凯瑟琳
Do you still drink your coffee with cinnamon, Katherine?

444
00:29:13,262 --> 00:29:15,262
- 有时候会 - 是的 她会
- Sometimes. - Yes, she does.

445
00:29:20,262 --> 00:29:23,261
我已经找到了红宝石和绿宝石的供货商
I've already sourced suppliers for rubies and emeralds, if you'd

446
00:29:23,262 --> 00:29:26,965
你希望我叫他们带着样品和报价来拜访我们吗
care for me to have them call on us with samples and prices,

447
00:29:26,966 --> 00:29:28,262
威斯顿先生?
 Mr Weston?

448
00:29:33,262 --> 00:29:36,261
我计划所有的柜台都用玻璃来制作
I'd planned for all the counters to be made of glass.

449
00:29:36,262 --> 00:29:40,261
还有吊灯 玻璃灯 整个商场要像宫殿一样
And chandeliers, glass lamps, the whole place is like a palace.

450
00:29:40,262 --> 00:29:45,261
闪亮的东西多了会显得太花哨
So much dazzle sounds positively garish.

451
00:29:45,262 --> 00:29:48,262
是啊 或许你是对的 先生
Yes, well, perhaps you're right, sir.

452
00:29:51,262 --> 00:29:55,261
我希望你旅行之后睡眠质量有所改善 凯瑟琳
I hope your sleep has improved after your travels, Katherine.

453
00:29:55,262 --> 00:29:59,261
我曾告诉她是因为咖啡的作用 但她不听劝
I used to tell her it's the coffee, but she wouldn't have it.

454
00:29:59,262 --> 00:30:03,261
如果女人可以不睡觉地活着...
If ever a woman could live without sleep...

455
00:30:03,262 --> 00:30:08,261
我曾被迫在花园里度过漫长的一夜
I was pressed into spending long nights in the garden.

456
00:30:08,262 --> 00:30:11,262
嗅着月光下木兰花香
The scent of magnolias under the moon...

457
00:30:19,262 --> 00:30:22,261
我觉得扩展区应该做成餐厅
I think the new extension should be a food hall,

458
00:30:22,262 --> 00:30:27,261
或卖鞋 或一些不带感情色彩的东西
or shoes or something without sentiment.

459
00:30:27,262 --> 00:30:30,261
我本来打算和你一起看看那里 莫里
I had meant to look over the place with you, Moray.

460
00:30:30,262 --> 00:30:33,043
但你当时不在 我们现在去看吧
But you were elsewhere. Let's take a look now.

461
00:30:33,044 --> 00:30:34,261
好 当然
Yes, of course,

462
00:30:34,262 --> 00:30:37,261
只是我不想把你的妻子单独留在这喝咖啡
although I would not wish to leave your wife with her coffee.

463
00:30:37,262 --> 00:30:38,262
我准备好走了
I am ready now.

464
00:30:48,262 --> 00:30:50,261
- 我要那双银色的鞋 - 我解释过了
- I want the silver shoes. - As I have explained,

465
00:30:50,262 --> 00:30:52,261
我们没有你的尺码 小姐
we don't have your size, miss.

466
00:30:52,262 --> 00:30:55,261
这双 我要这条带羽毛的裙子
These ones. I want the dress with the feathers.

467
00:30:55,262 --> 00:30:57,261
你不能穿这条有羽毛的裙子
You can't have the dress with the feathers.

468
00:30:57,262 --> 00:30:59,261
但那是我想要的
But that's what I want!

469
00:30:59,262 --> 00:31:01,261
妈妈说我想要什么都可以
Mama said I could have anything I wanted.

470
00:31:01,262 --> 00:31:04,261
你就是个被宠坏的无关紧要的人 这就是你
Oh, you're just a spoiled little NOTHING, that's what you are!

471
00:31:04,262 --> 00:31:07,261
你招招手 全世界都要围着你转!
You wave your hand and the rest of the world is supposed to pamper you!

472
00:31:07,262 --> 00:31:09,261
你想过没有?! 你是个小孩!
Do you even give a thought?! YOU ARE A CHILD!

473
00:31:09,262 --> 00:31:12,261
苏西 下楼去饭厅 马上!
Susy, go down to the refectory right now!

474
00:31:12,262 --> 00:31:14,261
快点 苏西! 下去
Come on, Susy! Go on.

475
00:31:15,262 --> 00:31:16,221
我要妈妈
I want Mama.

476
00:31:16,224 --> 00:31:18,261
我很抱歉 芙罗拉小姐 让我...
 I am so sorry, Miss Flora. Let me...

477
00:31:18,262 --> 00:31:21,262
不! 我要妈妈! 我要妈妈!
No! I want Mama! I want Mama!

478
00:31:22,262 --> 00:31:25,261
我很抱歉 夫人 不知道为什么...
I'm so sorry, ma'am. I don't know why...

479
00:31:25,262 --> 00:31:27,261
苏西一向是那样亲切的女孩!
Susy is usually such a sweet girl!

480
00:31:27,262 --> 00:31:32,261
我从来不知道她会... 她是我们的朋友
I've never before known her to... She's a friend,

481
00:31:32,262 --> 00:31:34,261
她平时那么善良又十分殷勤
usually full of kindness and so eager to please.

482
00:31:34,262 --> 00:31:38,547
达德利 请你把芙罗拉带出去一下好吗?
Dudley, do you think you could take Flora outside for a moment for me, please? 

483
00:31:38,548 --> 00:31:40,262
当然 夫人
Of course, ma'am.

484
00:31:52,262 --> 00:31:53,761
你准备怎么处理这事?
What do you propose to do?

485
00:31:53,762 --> 00:31:56,261
我会和莫里先生和达德利先生讲...
I will speak to Mr Moray and Mr Dudley...

486
00:31:56,262 --> 00:31:59,262
不 我想知道你准备怎么做
No. I want to know what YOU intend to do.

487
00:32:00,262 --> 00:32:04,497
你是女装部主管 不是吗?
You're Head of Ladieswear, are you not? 

488
00:32:04,498 --> 00:32:06,262
你要负责
You ARE responsible.

489
00:32:06,262 --> 00:32:10,261
是你让我的孩子受到如此羞辱
It was you who presided over this humiliation of my child.

490
00:32:10,262 --> 00:32:12,262
这个孩子!
THIS child!

491
00:32:13,262 --> 00:32:16,261
你准备怎么处理这个人?
What do you propose to do about this girl?

492
00:32:16,262 --> 00:32:18,261
- 她叫什么名字? - 苏西 夫人
- What is her name? - Susy, ma'am.

493
00:32:18,262 --> 00:32:21,262
那回答我 你的打算是什么?
Then answer me, what is your intention?

494
00:32:27,262 --> 00:32:30,261
我会跟苏西严肃说明
I will speak with Susy MOST severely.

495
00:32:30,262 --> 00:32:33,262
我会警告她对顾客这种态度...
I will warn her that to address customers in this way...

496
00:32:46,262 --> 00:32:47,761
我们不能做些什么吗? 
Can we not do something? 

497
00:32:47,762 --> 00:32:49,261
一定有什么原因使苏西...
There must be a reason Susy was...

498
00:32:49,262 --> 00:32:53,261
是有原因 她提升得太早了 她还没准备好
There IS a reason. Susy was promoted too early. She's not ready.

499
00:32:53,262 --> 00:32:55,011
但我们一定可以做点什么!
But there must be something we can do!

500
00:32:55,012 --> 00:32:57,228
现在是紧要关头 德妮丝 
These are the most delicate of times, Denise.

501
00:32:57,229 --> 00:32:59,261
我承受不起凯瑟琳的怒火
 I cannot afford to rile Katherine.

502
00:32:59,262 --> 00:33:01,261
我们必须顺着她意愿
We must be seen to follow her will.

503
00:33:01,262 --> 00:33:04,261
这是你的工作 德妮丝 你必须这么做
It's your job now, Denise. This has to be done.

504
00:33:04,262 --> 00:33:09,262
你想要这职位 这职位可不是办办茶宴就行
You wanted this position. It's not all tea parties.

505
00:33:34,262 --> 00:33:36,262
我试过了 苏西
I tried, Susy.

506
00:33:38,262 --> 00:33:39,261
我也不想这样
I wanted to avoid this.

507
00:33:39,262 --> 00:33:44,261
但你的所作所为使我没有退路
But what you did, you've left me with no choice.

508
00:33:44,262 --> 00:33:49,261
员工被解雇的时候必须马上离开宿舍
When a girl is dismissed, she must leave the premises right away.

509
00:33:49,262 --> 00:33:52,262
你必须收拾好行李... 然后走
You must collect your belongings... and go.

510
00:34:11,262 --> 00:34:13,166
或许别走远了 苏西 
Perhaps stay close by, Susy. 

511
00:34:13,167 --> 00:34:15,262
我们不知道会不会有变数
We never know what might change.

512
00:34:16,262 --> 00:34:18,262
我无处可去了
I have nowhere to stay.

513
00:34:19,262 --> 00:34:22,261
毕夏普街 迈希尔先生
Bishop Street. Mr Myhill.

514
00:34:22,262 --> 00:34:24,012
告诉他  乔纳斯・弗兰克斯说
Tell him jonas Franks said 

515
00:34:24,013 --> 00:34:25,262
你跟着他或许有个住处
you might find lodgings with him.

516
00:34:49,262 --> 00:34:51,261
蛋糕 夫人?
Cakes, madam?

517
00:34:51,262 --> 00:34:53,261
我像个女人吗?!
Do I look like a madam to you?!

518
00:34:53,262 --> 00:34:56,261
还有 我看这个更像脆骨而不是蛋糕
And THAT looks more like gristle to me than a cake.

519
00:34:56,262 --> 00:34:59,262
我在练习 您要茗茶吗? 还是阿萨姆茶?
I'm practising. Fine teas? Assam?

520
00:35:01,262 --> 00:35:04,261
大吉岭茶呢? 马德拉蛋糕呢?
Darjeeling? Madeira cake?

521
00:35:04,262 --> 00:35:07,262
我表现得还不赖吧?!
Aren't I the picture of restraint?!

522
00:35:30,262 --> 00:35:32,261
德妮丝!
Denise!

523
00:35:32,262 --> 00:35:35,262
德妮丝! 他们都明白苏西是自己引火上身
Denise! They all know that Susy brought this on herself.

524
00:35:37,262 --> 00:35:40,261
他们只是在演戏
Their reactions are for show.

525
00:35:40,262 --> 00:35:43,261
相互证明他们是亲信 他们在反抗我们
To prove to each other they are cronies. Them against us.

526
00:35:43,262 --> 00:35:46,261
这不是长久的 这是恐惧 仅此而已
It won't last. It's fear, that's all.

527
00:35:46,262 --> 00:35:49,261
你现在对他们的生活有影响了
You have influence on their lives now.

528
00:35:49,262 --> 00:35:52,261
你要表现得不是你的错 
Act as though you're not to blame. Don't apologise

529
00:35:52,262 --> 00:35:55,261
别为你的所作所为道歉 让他们说去吧 
for what you've done. Let them raise the matter if they want. Not you.

530
00:35:55,262 --> 00:35:58,261
表现得你有你的威严
Behave as though you take on your authority

531
00:35:58,262 --> 00:36:01,261
但他们要对自己的命运负责
but they are responsible for their own destiny.

532
00:36:01,262 --> 00:36:03,261
谢谢你 达德利先生
Thank you, Mr Dudley.

533
00:36:03,262 --> 00:36:06,261
你知道这事不怪你 不是吗 德妮丝?
You do know you're not to blame, don't you, Denise?

534
00:36:06,262 --> 00:36:07,261
但我本可以做更多的
But I might have done more.

535
00:36:07,262 --> 00:36:09,261
我看到苏西有什么烦心事
I saw there was something the matter with Susy.

536
00:36:09,262 --> 00:36:12,262
我希望我可以说一切都会好起来的
I wish I could say that it gets easier.

537
00:36:19,262 --> 00:36:23,261
克莱拉 有人看见你和威斯顿先生在海湾
Clara. You were seen in the bays with Mr Weston.

538
00:36:23,262 --> 00:36:25,261
你就是这样看我的吗?
Oh! Is that what you think of me?

539
00:36:25,262 --> 00:36:27,744
只要是穿着西装的男人我就会对他抛媚眼
Any man in a suit and I'll flutter me eyes

540
00:36:27,745 --> 00:36:29,262
然后掀起自己的裙摆吗?
 and lift me skirts?

541
00:36:30,262 --> 00:36:32,261
他想从你身上得到什么?
What did he want with you?

542
00:36:32,262 --> 00:36:33,352
他让我把他的名字
He asked to put his name 

543
00:36:33,353 --> 00:36:35,261
写在最后那首华尔兹的舞伴卡上
on me dance card for the last waltz,

544
00:36:35,262 --> 00:36:38,261
但我告诉他我已经有约了
but I told him I was all spoken for.

545
00:36:38,262 --> 00:36:40,261
那我不得不叫莫里先生来问你
Then I have no option but to ask

546
00:36:40,262 --> 00:36:43,262
为什么你会握着威斯顿先生的手
Mr Moray to ask you why you were holding Mr Weston's hand.

547
00:36:51,262 --> 00:36:53,262
他那时背痛
He had a pain in his back.

548
00:36:59,262 --> 00:37:00,262
非常痛
Terrible pain.

549
00:37:02,262 --> 00:37:05,262
而他的眼里却不止是痛苦
Something in his eyes. Something more than pain.

550
00:37:07,262 --> 00:37:10,261
- 他看起来就像... - 像什么?
- He looked like a man who'd... - Yes?

551
00:37:10,262 --> 00:37:14,261
像被人谋杀然后在等待死亡
Well, like a man who'd been murdered and was waiting to die,

552
00:37:14,262 --> 00:37:16,262
就像...
it was the same as...

553
00:37:18,262 --> 00:37:22,261
继续说下去克莱拉 你快说完了
Go on, Clara. You're almost done now.

554
00:37:22,262 --> 00:37:25,261
就像看烟火的那晚一样
It was the same as the night of the fireworks.

555
00:37:25,262 --> 00:37:26,262
它的噪音
The noise of it.

556
00:37:28,262 --> 00:37:31,262
让他像吓坏的小孩蜷缩着
He was cowering like a frightened child.

557
00:37:35,262 --> 00:37:38,261
乔纳斯先生 感觉不错吧?
Will that do you, Mr Jonas?

558
00:37:38,262 --> 00:37:42,261
又窥探到世上另一个阴暗的角落
Feel better now you've peered into another dark corner of this world?

559
00:37:42,262 --> 00:37:44,262
谢谢你 克莱拉
Thank you, Clara.

560
00:38:33,262 --> 00:38:35,261
当你对我隐瞒事情时
When you hide things from me, it is

561
00:38:35,262 --> 00:38:39,261
就是你想逃避这些事
because you prefer not to face them yourself.

562
00:38:39,262 --> 00:38:40,701
和乔纳斯躲躲闪闪的
Skulking around with Jonas.

563
00:38:40,702 --> 00:38:43,261
跟凯瑟琳调情 嘲弄汤姆・威斯顿
 Flirting with Katherine. Taunting Tom Weston.

564
00:38:43,262 --> 00:38:45,262
发生什么事了?
What's going on?

565
00:38:46,262 --> 00:38:48,261
无论你在做些什么
Whatever it is you are doing,

566
00:38:48,262 --> 00:38:49,534
我都知道你有多么想要回百货 
I know how much you want this store back, 

567
00:38:49,535 --> 00:38:51,261
但如果你的计划
but if your schemes

568
00:38:51,262 --> 00:38:55,261
对得起良心的话 你会告诉我的
can be admitted in good conscience, then you will tell me.

569
00:38:55,262 --> 00:39:00,261
莫里先生 你有消息要带去贝尔维尔大厅么?
Mr Moray, sir, you wanted a message taking out to Bellville Hall?

570
00:39:00,262 --> 00:39:03,262
今天不了 亚瑟 下次吧
Not today, Arthur. Perhaps some other time.

571
00:39:14,262 --> 00:39:15,716
德妮丝女士 
Miss Denise... 

572
00:39:15,717 --> 00:39:18,261
乔纳斯 拜托请叫我德妮丝
Please, Jonas, call me Denise.

573
00:39:18,262 --> 00:39:20,261
我更想尊重
I prefer to honour the tradition that has been

574
00:39:20,262 --> 00:39:22,261
流传了那么多年的传统
observed down the years.

575
00:39:22,262 --> 00:39:25,262
这是你赢得的 小姐 这个头衔代表着尊重
You've earned your place, ma'am, the title is a gesture of respect.

576
00:39:27,262 --> 00:39:29,261
好吧 谢谢你
Yes. Well, thank you.

577
00:39:29,262 --> 00:39:30,595
恕我直言...
If I may... 

578
00:39:30,596 --> 00:39:33,261
对于我们这种地方 忠诚很重要
there is much talk of loyalty in a place like this.

579
00:39:33,262 --> 00:39:35,261
没有比它更重要的
Most of it is talk and no more.

580
00:39:35,262 --> 00:39:37,261
我真的不希望苏西...
I had no wish for Susy to...

581
00:39:37,262 --> 00:39:42,261
小姐 请让我说下去 忠诚像是特别的礼物
Please, ma'am, let me go on. Loyalty is a special gift.

582
00:39:42,262 --> 00:39:46,261
是唯一能做到凝聚人心的 但需要你鼓起勇气
It binds people like no other cause. But it CAN take courage.

583
00:39:46,262 --> 00:39:49,511
如果你找得到办法让苏西复职
If you can find a way to win Susy her place back here in the store, 

584
00:39:49,512 --> 00:39:51,261
你就证明了
you would have proven that you're

585
00:39:51,262 --> 00:39:53,261
你是这里所有员工的忠诚伙伴
the staunchest ally of everyone who works here.

586
00:39:53,262 --> 00:39:55,696
你会变成他们权益的捍卫者
You would be their champion.

587
00:39:55,697 --> 00:39:57,261
但这不可能啊
It is not possible.

588
00:39:57,262 --> 00:39:59,880
不是你亲口和莫里先生说
Was it not you yourself told Mr Moray

589
00:39:59,881 --> 00:40:02,261
"这必须可能"的吗?
 it must be possible?

590
00:40:02,262 --> 00:40:03,261
但我不知道该怎么做
But I don't know how.

591
00:40:03,262 --> 00:40:05,261
我也不知道 小姐
 Nor do I, ma'am.

592
00:40:05,264 --> 00:40:07,262
但我相信你会想到方法的
But I trust you'll find a way.

593
00:40:19,262 --> 00:40:20,262
杜松子酒
Gin.

594
00:40:34,262 --> 00:40:36,261
没想到会在这里见到你
I didn't expect to see you here.

595
00:40:36,262 --> 00:40:38,262
真希望我也能这么说 妈
I wish I could say the same of you, Ma.

596
00:40:41,262 --> 00:40:45,262
我留下来是想和你再谈一下
I stayed so that I might speak with you one more time.

597
00:40:54,262 --> 00:40:57,261
苏西我不怪你恨我
I don't blame you for hating me, Susy.

598
00:40:57,262 --> 00:41:01,261
把自己的孩子送走一定是世上最严重的罪
It has to be the worst crime in the world to give your child away.

599
00:41:01,262 --> 00:41:02,976
我知道你不会相信我
I know you don't believe me, 

600
00:41:02,977 --> 00:41:05,262
但我是为了你才这么做的
but I did it for you.

601
00:41:09,262 --> 00:41:11,840
你怨我的理由 
The reasons you use to blame me

602
00:41:11,841 --> 00:41:16,261
就是我不得不送走你的原因
 are the reasons that i had to give you away.

603
00:41:16,262 --> 00:41:18,262
跟着我这样的妈妈你会过怎样的生活?
What kind of life would you have with a ma like me?

604
00:41:20,262 --> 00:41:25,261
每天我都告诉自己不能再喝醉
Every day I promise myself I won't be drunk,

605
00:41:26,262 --> 00:41:30,261
但是每天都会发现自己手中又拿着酒杯
and then every day I find meself with a glass in me hand.

606
00:41:30,262 --> 00:41:33,261
我不得不放手让你离开我
I had to free you from me and the only way that

607
00:41:33,262 --> 00:41:35,262
又继续再喝酒
I could do that was to have another drink inside me.

608
00:41:37,262 --> 00:41:40,261
我是对你撒了谎
I have lied to you, yes.

609
00:41:40,262 --> 00:41:44,261
但你老实回答我 你如果留在我身边
But you tell me, if you can tell the truth, would it've been

610
00:41:44,262 --> 00:41:48,262
会比现在过的好么?
a better life if you'd stayed with me than the one that you've had?

611
00:41:52,262 --> 00:41:57,262
不 不会
No. No, it wouldn't.

612
00:42:00,262 --> 00:42:05,261
我人生里唯一能给你的
There's only one thing in this life that I could give you

613
00:42:05,262 --> 00:42:08,262
就是放手让你离开我
and that was to be free of me.

614
00:42:11,262 --> 00:42:15,261
虽然我知道 或许有那么一天
I knew, though, that there'd come the day

615
00:42:15,262 --> 00:42:17,262
我可以看着你
when I'd look at ya...

616
00:42:19,262 --> 00:42:22,262
告诉你我爱你
..and I'd tell ya I love you.

617
00:42:37,262 --> 00:42:41,262
我... 我爱你 妈妈
I... I love you, Ma.

618
00:42:58,262 --> 00:43:02,261
我为你能在那种地方工作而骄傲
I'm so proud of you working in that place.

619
00:43:02,262 --> 00:43:03,262
那儿多豪华
It's so grand.

620
00:43:07,262 --> 00:43:11,261
我不在那里工作了
I don't work there no more.

621
00:43:11,262 --> 00:43:16,262
- 为什么? - 我被解雇了 自找的
- Why? - I was sacked. Made a disgrace of myself.

622
00:43:18,262 --> 00:43:22,261
不会的 我的苏西不会的
No, not you. Not my Susy.

623
00:43:22,262 --> 00:43:24,261
我冒犯了一个小孩
I offended a child.

624
00:43:24,262 --> 00:43:28,011
天啊 他们就没点宽容的心吗?!
Oh, have they no mercy?! 

625
00:43:28,012 --> 00:43:30,261
他们该有多卑鄙啊?!
What kind of swines are they?!

626
00:43:30,262 --> 00:43:32,262
不是的... 都过去了 妈妈
No, it... it's done now, Ma.

627
00:43:41,262 --> 00:43:43,261
我再去拿杯酒
I'm just going to get one more.

628
00:43:43,262 --> 00:43:45,262
女儿认回我可不是天天都有的事
It's not every day you get your daughter back.

629
00:43:56,262 --> 00:43:58,262
干杯
Cheers.

630
00:44:04,262 --> 00:44:06,261
让他们下地狱去
Well, to hell with them.

631
00:44:06,262 --> 00:44:07,822
他们都不值得我用口水吐他们
They're not worth a spit 

632
00:44:07,823 --> 00:44:09,262
竟能对我女儿做这样的事
if they'd do that to my girl.

633
00:44:19,262 --> 00:44:20,262
我现在在干嘛?
What am I doing?

634
00:44:22,262 --> 00:44:25,261
我为了什么要和你坐在一起?
What am I doing here sitting here with you?

635
00:44:25,262 --> 00:44:30,262
没有变 你什么都没变 还是酒 够了!
It's the same, it's always the same, the drink, that's all!

636
00:44:31,262 --> 00:44:34,262
苏西! 苏西!
Susy! Susy!

637
00:44:36,262 --> 00:44:41,261
夫人 午安 您是想喝阿萨姆茶呢?
Good afternoon, madam. Assam?

638
00:44:41,262 --> 00:44:42,262
还是大吉岭茶?
Darjeeling?

639
00:44:44,262 --> 00:44:47,261
苏西你到这干嘛?
Susy, what are you doing here?

640
00:44:47,262 --> 00:44:49,261
哦 我忘了!
Oh! I forgot!

641
00:44:49,262 --> 00:44:52,261
我... 我急着回家却忘了我不住在这了
I... I was hurrying home and I forgot I don't live here no more.

642
00:44:52,262 --> 00:44:54,261
噢 你最好在乔纳斯先生看到你前离开
Oh, you best go, girl, before Mr Jonas finds ya.

643
00:44:54,262 --> 00:44:58,262
苏西不要走 我有话想跟你说
Susy! Don't go! I want to speak to you.

644
00:45:02,262 --> 00:45:04,262
你想复职么?
Do you want your position back?

645
00:45:05,262 --> 00:45:09,261
我是说 你想试着争取复职么?
What I mean is, do you want to try and get it back?

646
00:45:09,262 --> 00:45:10,961
当然
I should say so.

647
00:45:10,962 --> 00:45:14,261
我不敢保证一定会成功 这需要我们鼓起勇气
I can't promise we'll manage it, it'll take courage.

648
00:45:14,264 --> 00:45:16,962
你可以按我说的做么?
Will you do exactly as I say?

649
00:45:18,262 --> 00:45:19,261
